   390	## Obsidian support
   391	
   392	When `vault.renderMode` is `obsidian`, the plugin writes Obsidian-friendly
   393	Markdown and can optionally use the official `obsidian` CLI.
   394	
   395	Supported workflows include:
   396	
   397	- status probing
   398	- vault search
   399	- opening a page
   400	- invoking an Obsidian command
   401	- jumping to the daily note
   402	
   403	This is optional. The wiki still works in native mode without Obsidian.
   404	
   405	## Recommended workflow
   406	
   407	1. Keep your active memory plugin for recall/promotion/dreaming.
   408	2. Enable `memory-wiki`.
   409	3. Start with `isolated` mode unless you explicitly want bridge mode.
   410	4. Use `wiki_search` / `wiki_get` when provenance matters.
   411	5. Use `wiki_apply` for narrow syntheses or metadata updates.
   412	6. Run `wiki_lint` after meaningful changes.
   413	7. Turn on dashboards if you want stale/contradiction visibility.
   414	
   415	## Related docs
   416	
   417	- [Memory Overview](/concepts/memory)
   418	- [CLI: memory](/cli/memory)
   419	- [CLI: wiki](/cli/wiki)
   420	- [Plugin SDK overview](/plugins/sdk-overview)

